Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.00,0:00:08.06,灰英字,,0,0,0,,When I've been building applications with large language models
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.06,0:00:10.24,灰英字,,0,0,0,,I don't think I've ever come to the prompt that I ended up
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.24,0:00:13.56,灰英字,,0,0,0,,using in the final application on my first attempt
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.56,0:00:15.18,灰英字,,0,0,0,,And this isn't what matters
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.18,0:00:19.86,灰英字,,0,0,0,,As long as you have a good process to iteratively make your prompt better
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.86,0:00:22.10,灰英字,,0,0,0,,then you'll be able to come to something that
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.10,0:00:24.68,灰英字,,0,0,0,,works well for the task you want to achieve
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.68,0:00:28.00,灰英字,,0,0,0,,You may have heard me say that when I train a machine learning model
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.00,0:00:29.92,灰英字,,0,0,0,,it almost never works the first time
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.92,0:00:33.36,灰英字,,0,0,0,,In fact, I'm very surprised that the first model I trained works
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.36,0:00:37.16,灰英字,,0,0,0,,I think we're prompting, the odds of it working the first time is maybe a little bit
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.16,0:00:39.64,灰英字,,0,0,0,,higher but as she's saying
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.64,0:00:42.06,灰英字,,0,0,0,,doesn't matter if the first prompt works
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.06,0:00:46.64,灰英字,,0,0,0,,what matters most is the process for getting to prompts that works for your application
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.64,0:00:49.52,灰英字,,0,0,0,,So with that, let's jump into the code and let me show you
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.52,0:00:53.68,灰英字,,0,0,0,,some frameworks to think about how to iteratively develop a prompt
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.68,0:00:57.84,灰英字,,0,0,0,,All right. So if you've taken a machine learning class with me
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.84,0:01:02.76,灰英字,,0,0,0,,before you may have seen me use a diagram saying that with machine learning development
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.76,0:01:06.44,灰英字,,0,0,0,,you often have an idea and then implement it
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.44,0:01:08.78,灰英字,,0,0,0,,So write the code, get the data
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.78,0:01:12.72,灰英字,,0,0,0,,train your model and that gives you an experimental result
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.72,0:01:14.38,灰英字,,0,0,0,,And you can then look at that output
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.38,0:01:16.08,灰英字,,0,0,0,,maybe do error analysis
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.08,0:01:17.76,灰英字,,0,0,0,,figure out where it's working or not working
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.76,0:01:19.76,灰英字,,0,0,0,,and then maybe even change your idea of
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.76,0:01:23.12,灰英字,,0,0,0,,exactly what problem you want to solve or how to approach it
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.12,0:01:25.68,灰英字,,0,0,0,,And then change implementation and run
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.68,0:01:27.92,灰英字,,0,0,0,,another experiment and so on and iterate over and
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.92,0:01:31.10,灰英字,,0,0,0,,over to get to an effective machine learning model
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.10,0:01:33.16,灰英字,,0,0,0,,If you're not familiar with machine learning
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.16,0:01:35.24,灰英字,,0,0,0,,haven't seen this diagram before, don't worry about it
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.24,0:01:38.20,灰英字,,0,0,0,,Not that important for the rest of this presentation
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.20,0:01:44.88,灰英字,,0,0,0,,But when you are writing prompts to develop an application using an LLM
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.88,0:01:48.30,灰英字,,0,0,0,,the process can be quite similar
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.30,0:01:50.58,灰英字,,0,0,0,,where you have an idea for what you want to do
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.58,0:01:52.04,灰英字,,0,0,0,,the task you want to complete
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.04,0:01:55.88,灰英字,,0,0,0,,and you can then take a first attempt at writing
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.88,0:01:59.40,灰英字,,0,0,0,,a prompt that hopefully is clear and specific
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.40,0:02:01.56,灰英字,,0,0,0,,and maybe if appropriate
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.56,0:02:04.12,灰英字,,0,0,0,,gives the system time to think
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.12,0:02:07.76,灰英字,,0,0,0,,And then you can run it and see what result you get
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.76,0:02:10.12,灰英字,,0,0,0,,And if it doesn't work well enough the first time
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.12,0:02:13.84,灰英字,,0,0,0,,then the iterative process of figuring out why the instructions
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.84,0:02:15.96,灰英字,,0,0,0,,for example, were not clear enough or why it
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.96,0:02:17.76,灰英字,,0,0,0,,didn't give the algorithm enough time to think
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.76,0:02:19.36,灰英字,,0,0,0,,allows you to refine the idea
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.36,0:02:21.26,灰英字,,0,0,0,,refine the prompt, and so on
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.26,0:02:23.24,灰英字,,0,0,0,,and to go around this loop multiple times
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.24,0:02:26.20,灰英字,,0,0,0,,until you end up with a prompt that works for your application
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.20,0:02:32.32,灰英字,,0,0,0,,This too is why I personally have not paid as much attention to
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.32,0:02:35.84,灰英字,,0,0,0,,the Internet articles that say 30 perfect prompts because I think
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.84,0:02:39.72,灰英字,,0,0,0,,there probably isn't a perfect prompt for everything under the sun
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.72,0:02:42.00,灰英字,,0,0,0,,It's more important that you have a process for
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.00,0:02:45.44,灰英字,,0,0,0,,developing a good prompt for your specific application
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.44,0:02:49.00,灰英字,,0,0,0,,So let's look at an example together in code
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.00,0:02:51.40,灰英字,,0,0,0,,I have here the starter code that you saw in
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.40,0:02:54.44,灰英字,,0,0,0,,the previous videos have been import openai and port is
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.44,0:02:58.24,灰英字,,0,0,0,,Here we get the OpenAI API key
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.24,0:03:02.28,灰英字,,0,0,0,,and this is the same helper function that you saw as last time
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.28,0:03:08.44,灰英字,,0,0,0,,And I'm going to use as the running example in this video
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.44,0:03:12.68,灰英字,,0,0,0,,the task of summarizing a fact sheet for a chair
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.68,0:03:16.28,灰英字,,0,0,0,,So let me just paste that in here
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.28,0:03:19.72,灰英字,,0,0,0,,and feel free to pause the video and read
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.72,0:03:23.12,灰英字,,0,0,0,,this more carefully in the notebook on the left if you want
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.12,0:03:26.80,灰英字,,0,0,0,,But here's a fact sheet for a chair with a description saying it's part of
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.80,0:03:30.32,灰英字,,0,0,0,,a beautiful family of mid-century inspired and so on
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.32,0:03:31.92,灰英字,,0,0,0,,talks about the construction
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.92,0:03:34.68,灰英字,,0,0,0,,has the dimensions, options for the chair
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.68,0:03:38.24,灰英字,,0,0,0,,materials, and so on. It comes from Italy
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.24,0:03:42.96,灰英字,,0,0,0,,So let's say you want to take this fact sheet and help
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.96,0:03:47.88,灰英字,,0,0,0,,a marketing team write a description for an online retail website
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.88,0:03:50.84,灰英字,,0,0,0,,Let me just quickly run these three
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.84,0:03:57.76,灰英字,,0,0,0,,and then we'll come up with a prompt as follows
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.76,0:04:01.44,灰英字,,0,0,0,,I'll just paste this in
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.44,0:04:03.40,灰英字,,0,0,0,,So my prompt here says
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.40,0:04:05.88,灰英字,,0,0,0,,your task is to help a marketing team create
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.88,0:04:08.96,灰英字,,0,0,0,,a description for a retail website or product based on a techno fact sheet
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.96,0:04:11.20,灰英字,,0,0,0,,write a product description, and so on
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.20,0:04:16.88,灰英字,,0,0,0,,So this is my first attempt to explain the task to the large language model
